      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to cover his face; with a veil, or linen cloth, to blindfold: him, as a person unworthy to behold the light: or rather, in order to make sport with him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to buffet him; with their double fists; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to say unto him, prophesy. The Arabic version adds, \"unto us, O Christ, who it is that hath buffeted thee now?\" that gave thee the last blow? and to the same purpose the Ethiopic. The Persic version adds, \"and deliver thyself\"; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands. The Syriac version renders it, \"on his cheeks\": they gave him slaps on the face. These were the officers of the high priest, that used him in this indecent manner. This clause is omitted in the Ethiopic version. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands. The Syriac version renders it, \"on his cheeks\": they gave him slaps on the face. These were the officers of the high priest, that used him in this indecent manner. This clause is omitted in the Ethiopic version. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
