        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to spit on him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] In those rough ages a prisoner under sentence of death was ever delivered over to the mockery of his guards. It was so now with the Holy One of God. Spitting was regarded by the Jews as an expression of the greatest contempt (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 12:14",
        "children": []
